File: api/proto/gophkeeper/v1/register.proto
Package: gophkeeper.v1
Role: API Contract
Purpose: Defines two-step passwordless first-device registration protocol with challenge-response SSH authentication.
Service: Registration
RPCs: RegisterBegin(RegisterBeginRequest) returns (RegisterBeginResponse); RegisterFinish(RegisterFinishRequest) returns (RegisterFinishResponse).
RegisterBeginRequest: username string, ssh_public_key bytes. RegisterBeginResponse: user_id string, account_salt bytes, session_id string, server_nonce bytes.
RegisterFinishRequest: user_id string, session_id string, auth_challenge_signature bytes, device_id string, account_bootstrap_envelope bytes, device_master_key_envelope bytes, csr bytes.
RegisterFinishResponse: client_certificate bytes, ca_chain bytes.
Security Constraints: RegisterFinish verifies auth_challenge_signature over ChallengePayload(register). Submits cloud account_bootstrap_envelope and local device_master_key_envelope. CSR is public key only. Marks challenge session consumed.

File: api/proto/gophkeeper/v1/attach_device.proto
Package: gophkeeper.v1
Role: API Contract
Purpose: Defines three-step device attachment protocol ensuring withholding of account secrets until SSH possession is proven.
Service: DeviceAttachment
RPCs: AttachDeviceBegin(AttachDeviceBeginRequest) returns (AttachDeviceBeginResponse); AttachDeviceAuth(AttachDeviceAuthRequest) returns (AttachDeviceAuthResponse); AttachDeviceFinish(AttachDeviceFinishRequest) returns (AttachDeviceFinishResponse).
AttachDeviceBeginRequest: ssh_public_key bytes. AttachDeviceBeginResponse: user_id string, session_id string, server_nonce bytes.
AttachDeviceAuthRequest: user_id string, session_id string, auth_challenge_signature bytes. AttachDeviceAuthResponse: account_salt bytes, account_bootstrap_envelope bytes.
AttachDeviceFinishRequest: user_id string, session_id string, device_id string, device_master_key_envelope bytes, csr bytes.
AttachDeviceFinishResponse: client_certificate bytes, ca_chain bytes.
Security Constraints: AttachDeviceBegin explicitly withholds account_salt and cloud envelope. AttachDeviceAuth releases secrets only after signature validation. AttachDeviceFinish registers container device_id and issues mTLS certificate. Prevents session reuse.
